Astera Labs (ALAB) has a robust growth trajectory with an attractive entry point due to the recent stock pullback and multiple potential tailwinds, Morgan Stanley said in a note emailed Wednesday.

Tailwinds include "demand for artificial intelligence connectivity solutions, application-specific integrated circuit ramps, new products and broadening retimer applications," Morgan Stanley said.

Astera is expected to achieve over 50% growth in 2025 despite concerns over "less content in NVIDIA's (NVDA) rack-scale systems," the investment firm said.

Morgan Stanley said it expects Astera to trade at a premium due to its "unique" AI exposure.

Morgan Stanley upgraded Astera's rating to overweight from equalweight and kept the price target at $55.
